Make MDNET serverless
======================

Change code to run without server part. Content files are located at github/gitlab or similar service.
As a client I can open NDNet in browser and configure which sources I want to read. Source points to 
search-index.json which provides indexed files. It should be possible for user to give a source 
local name (like project-documentation for example). When searching the content, all sources should be
queried, in result window it should be mentioned what is the source (by given local name )for found result.

